The Niteshift Guvnor, Ken Calebs Olumese, has put the edifice that used to house The Coliseum in the Opebi area of Ikeja up for lease. According to a report by Yes International, Olumese sealed the lease deal weeks back with a showbiz entrepreneur, who has chosen to remain anonymous. The Coliseum, until it was shut down in 2014, was unarguably Nigeria’s No. 1 celebrity hangout.   Having s3x on first date doesn’t make you cheap – Blessing…     Social media reacts as Davido reveals 2022 motto     Wife celebrates Seun Kuti at 39   The nightclub began operations on the top floor of a rented apartment in Opebi (where Tastee Fried Chicken used to be). It opened in 1988 and was then known as The Niteshift. - Advertisement - It, however, moved to its permanent structure in 1999, under a new name – The Coliseum. The Niteshift and The Coliseum cemented Guvnor Olumese’s 30-year reign as a showbiz impresario before his retirement.